From an {{bor|la|osc|-}}-{{bor|la|xum|-}} language, from {{der|la|itc-pro|*lukʷos}}, metathesis of {{der|la|ine-pro|*wĺ̥kʷos}}. The */kʷ → p/ change is regular in Osco-Umbrian, but absent from Latin.<ref>'''2003''', ''Indo-European Linguistics'', Michael Meier-Brügger, Matthias Fritz, and Manfred Mayrhofe (p. 99).</ref> Another example of a borrowing with that shift is {{m|la|popīna}}.

Cognates include {{cog|grc|λύκος}}, {{cog|sa|वृक}}, {{cog|ang|wulf}}, and {{cog|cu|влькъ}}. {{doublet|la|Lycus}}; not cognate to {{nc|la|vulpēs||fox}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{la-IPA|lupus}}

===Noun===
{{la-noun|lupus<2>|f=lupa}}

# {{lb|la|zoology}} [[wolf]] (''[[Canis lupus|C. lupus]]'')
#: {{ux|la|Homō hominī '''lupus'''.
|A man is a '''wolf''' to another man.}}
# {{lb|la|zoology}} an [[animal]] which [[act]]s in the [[savage]] [[manner]] of a [[wolf]], ''[[particularly]]:''
## [[pike]] ([[Esocidae]])
## [[wolffish]] ([[Anarhichadidae]])
## an [[uncertain]] [[kind]] of [[spider]]
# {{lb|la|carpentry}} a [[tool]] which is [[shape]]d like a [[wolf]]'s [[tooth]], ''[[particularly]]:''
## a [[kind]] of [[bit]]
## a [[kind]] of [[handsaw]]
## a [[kind]] of [[hook]] [[use]]d for [[hoist]]ing [[object]]s
# {{lb|la|botany}} [[hops]] (''[[Humulus lupulus|H. lupulus]]'')

